properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 13 at 3:27AM CST until February 14 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Bitter Cold Air into Friday Morning...

.An arctic airmass will remain in place across central Iowa into
Friday morning. The combination of very cold temperatures and the
wind will produce bitter cold wind chills.

* WHAT...For the first Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills
with values as low as 30 below zero. For the second Wind Chill
Advisory, very cold wind chills expected with values as low as
25 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of central Iowa.

* WHEN...For the first Wind Chill Advisory, until noon today. For
the second Wind Chill Advisory, from 9 PM this evening to 10 AM
Friday.

* IMPACTS...The bitter cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 AM CST FRIDAY
